  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA226-kiḷavi">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷ vaṉpoṟai yetirmoḻintatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how SHE who had become weak during the time of separation spoke in the face of consolation.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA226">
<l>            marañcā maruntuṅ koḷḷār mānta</l>
<l>            rurañcāc ceyyā ruyartavam vaḷaṅkoṭ</l>
<l>            poṉṉuṅ koḷḷār maṉṉar naṉṉuta</l>
<l>            ṉānta muṇmaiyi ṉuḷamē yataṉāṟ</l>
<l>            ṟāñcey poruḷaḷa vaṟiyā tāṅkacin </l>
<l>            teṉṟūḻ niṟuppa nīḷiṭai yoḻiyac</l>
<l>            ceṉṟōr maṉṟanaṅ kātala reṉṟu</l>
<l>            miṉṉa nilaimait teṉpa</l>
<l>            veṉṉōru maṟipaviv vulakat tāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>People won’t take away [so much] medicine that the tree dies,</l>
<l>and they won’t do [so much] high penance that [their] strength is exhausted,</l>
<l>and the king won’t take [so much] gold that he takes away [all] the wealth,</l>
<l rend="indent4">o you of good forehead.<note place="foot">Strange is the distribution of -<term xml:lang="ta">um</term> here. We have <term xml:lang="ta">maruntum</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">poṉṉum</term>, but no <term xml:lang="ta">tavamum</term>. Do we nevertheless have to coordinate all three sentences?</note></l>
<l>We are [just] because of his existence.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Therefore,</l>
<l rend="indent">even when it is said that certainly our lover is one who has gone</l>
<l rend="indent2">for the long way to stay behind, while the sun is balancing,</l>
<l rend="indent">he himself melting, not knowing the measure of the wealth</l>
<l rend="indent">to be made by him,</l>
<l>thus [is] the state of affairs, they say.</l>
<l>Whoever [there is] knows it, in this world.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="7f.b">
    <l>certainly our lover is one who has gone (...),</l>
    <l>thus [is] always the state of affairs, they say.<note place="foot">Thus T.V.G.’s interpretation of <term xml:lang="ta">eṉṟum</term>. The a version seems to me preferable because it avoids an unmarked end of a sentence (though in this text, to be sure, there are so many unmarked ends that this argument can not be counted as strong).</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
